	<system>// Place template instantiations here.
jobber1 = jobber();
jobber2 = jobber();
jobber3 = jobber();
jobber4 = jobber();

// List one or more processes to be composed into a system.
system jobber1, jobber2, jobber3, jobber4, hammer, mallet;
    </system>
	<queries>
		<query>
			<formula>A[] not(jobber2.easy and jobber2.hard)
			</formula>
			<comment>Assurance of not occuring an incident:  jobber 2 will never get an easy and hard task simultanously.
			</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>E&lt;&gt; (jobber3.easy | jobber3.average | jobber3.hard)
			</formula>
			<comment>UZAIR says that there exists a state when the jobber3 is performing a task.
			</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>E&lt;&gt; not (mallet.taken &amp; hammer.taken)
			</formula>
			<comment>According to UZAIR, there exists a state where both the resources are not consumed.
			</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>E&lt;&gt; jobber1.easy
			</formula>
			<comment>Livenes: jobber1 gets sometime an easy task.
			</comment>
		</query>
	</queries>
